===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} '''[[connexion]]''' < {{L.}} '''[[connexio#Latin|connexio]]''' "a [[conclusion]], [[binding]] [[together]]" < '''[[connecto#Latin|connectō]]''', an alternative spelling of '''[[conecto#Latin|cōnectō]]''' "I [[bind]] [[together]]" < compound of '''[[co-#Latin|co-]]''' "[[together]]" and '''[[necto#Latin|nectō]]''' "I [[bind]]"

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# {{uncountable}} The act of [[connect]]ing.
# {{countable}} The point at which two or more things are connected.
# {{countable}} A feeling of understanding and ease of communication between two or more people.
# {{countable}} An established telephone call.

